ISLAMABAD, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan confirmed 76 new COVID-19 cases and no more death from the pandemic during the past 24 hours, the country's ministry of health said on Saturday. According to data released by the ministry, the country's total tally of COVID-19 cases has risen to 1,527,151, including 1,490,947 recoveries. Currently there are 5,841 active cases recorded in the Asian country, including 211 patients who are in critical condition. Pakistan's southern Sindh province is the most affected region in terms of the number of cases, with 576,517 infections in total, followed by the eastern Punjab province which has reported 505,614 cases so far.  â– 